/* SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
 * Copyright 2026 Rhett Creighton
 *
 * Shared consensus-verify BENCHMARK fixture: a REAL Equihash (200,9)
 * witness — the mainnet PoW parameter set, the dominant per-block PoW
 * cost. Used by BOTH:
 *   - the crypto-verify microbenchmark (src/main.c `-bench-crypto-verify`),
 *     which times check_equihash_solution() over this witness, and
 *   - the hermetic teeth test (lib/test/src/test_verify_bench_selftest.c),
 *     which asserts the benched verify returns true on this witness and
 *     false on a one-index-perturbed copy — so the benchmark can never
 *     "get fast" by benching a broken/no-op verifier.
 *
 * The witness was produced ONCE, offline, by the in-tree Wagner solver
 * (lib/crypto/src/equihash.c::equihash_basic_solve) over the fixed
 * synthetic header below (nonce byte0=0). Solving 200,9 costs ~36 s and
 * ~9 GB RAM, so the answer is baked here rather than re-solved at run
 * time; VERIFY of a baked witness is microseconds and fully hermetic.
 * The solve is deterministic in the header (the algorithm has no RNG),
 * so this fixture is reproducible: re-run tools/gen with the same header
 * and you get these same bytes. Verification does not depend on the PoW
 * target — only that the bytes are a valid Equihash answer for the
 * personalised BLAKE2b state seeded by this header.
 */
